==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pimpernel
<hw>Pim"per*nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pimprenelle</ets>; cf. Sp. <ets>pimpinela</ets>, It.
<ets>pimpinella</ets>; perh. from LL. <ets>bipinnella</ets>, for
<ets>bipinnula</ets> two-winged, equiv. to L. <ets>bipennis</ets>;
<ets>bis</ets> twice + <ets>penna</ets> feather, wing. Cf. <er>Pen</er>
a feather.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant of the genus
<gen>Anagallis</gen>, of which one species (<spn>Anagallis
arvensis</spn>) has small flowers, usually scarlet, but sometimes
purple, blue, or white, which speedily close at the approach of bad
weather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Water pimpernel</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Brookweed</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pimpillo</ent>⟦br⟧
